OL,3,CFamily's anger after severely autistic
OL,4,Cwoman offered dementia care home place
OL,6,FThe family of Sophie Appleton speak to
OL,7,Freporter Amelia Beckett
OL,9,FThe family of a severely autistic
OL,10,Fwoman who cannot live independently
OL,11,Fsay it is "awful" that she was offered
OL,12,Fa place in a dementia care home
OL,13,Finstead of accommodation for adults
OL,14,Fwith learning difficulties.
OL,16,FSophie Appleton, 52, has limited
OL,17,Fcommunication and social skills and is
OL,18,Funable to care for herself. She has
OL,19,Flived with her parents, Pat and Dick,
OL,20,Fall her life.
